   public static String evaluateOneHandOfPoker(){
      
      Deck.reset();
      Deck.shuffle();
      
      Deck.deal(); // loop 5 times
      
      // 52
      
      
      // This creates a new deck of cards, shuffles the cards,
      // deals 5 cards to an array of cards, sorts the cards,
      // calls up to nine other methods to check what type of
      // hand was dealt, and returns a String (such as "Full House")
      // to indicate which type of hand it was.  This is a lot,
      // but much of it is done through other methods you will write.
      // Advice: Use Arrays.sort() to sort your cards.  It will be
      // much easier to determine the hand type if the hand is first
      // sorted.  You do not need to know how to do the sorting. Just call the method.  
   }
   
